<Class name="CM_FutureStorage" id="9cf6b562-ec11-4f2c-b35c-51dc6c61b4af">
    <superclass name="CM_Storage"/>
    <persistentAllowed/>
    <sharedTransientAllowed/>
    <subclassPersistentAllowed/>
    <subclassSharedTransientAllowed/>
    <subclassTransientAllowed/>
    <transientAllowed/>
    <text>CCMS DPH 2278


Rules
1. Cargo must be onsite
2. Cargo must have a matching Storage Detail with future storage mappings.
3. Anniversary date must be equal or greater than the free storage expiry.
4. If there is already a BGP the re-evaluate future storage does nothing.
5. If the cargo has a future storage transaction then it has started and we must not change the anniversary date. 
		If the cargo has a future storage transaction the anniversary date is only set by the BGP request.
		If the cargo does not have a future storage transaction the anniversary date is set by the re eval process.
</text>
    <DbClassMap file="storage"/>
    <PrimAttribute name="chargeDateTime" id="8d01c8a5-014e-491a-b85e-ea845f42f649">
